data.title: Core-Based Statistical Areas
data.meta_description: CBSA (Core-Based Statistical Areas) Database. Formerly known as MSA (Metropolitan Statistical Areas)
data.text:
Data Format - CSV: Comma-Separated Values (CSV) Text File

CBSA ZIP Code: Official U.S. Postal Service five digit ZIP Code (ZIP to CBSA)

City: Official city name used by the U.S. Postal Service

State: Official U.S. Postal Service State Abbreviation

County: The name of the county in which the ZIP Code is found.

CBSA Code: Geographic location code as defined by the Office of Management and Budget

CBSA Name: Geographic location name as defined by the Office of Management and Budget

CBSA Type: A CBSA sub-classification:

Micro - 10,000 to 50,000 population

Metro - 50,000 + population

Rank: A sequence number for each record indicating the greatest population to the least

CBSA Est. Population: Current U.S. Census population estimates per CBSA Code

Division Code: Code assigned to geographic areas having more than 2.5 million people

Division Name: Name assigned to Division Code
